# Project Cursor Rules

## 🏗️ Tech Stack & Architecture

- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, internal UI kit (`@repo/ui`, shadcn-derived)
- **State & Data**: NextAuth (JWT sessions) + TanStack Query (fetch/cache); SWR is allowed for selective cache invalidation
- **HTTP Client**: Axios via a single `ApiClient` abstraction
- **Validation**: Zod (frontend) + class-validator/class-transformer (backend DTOs)
- **Backend**: NestJS 11 (modules/services/controllers), Prisma ORM, JWT auth (Passport strategy)
- **Docs**: Swagger/OpenAPI (auto via `@nestjs/swagger` plugin)
- **Email**: `@nestjs-modules/mailer` with HTML templates
- **DB**: PostgreSQL via Prisma; shared enums/types in `@repo/db` and `@repo/shared-types`
- **Tooling**: pnpm workspaces, Turbo, Prettier + Tailwind plugin, ESLint (flat configs)

## 📋 General Coding Standards

### Code Quality Requirements
- ALWAYS write TypeScript
- Follow ESLint and Prettier; fix all warnings where feasible
- Follow Conventional Commits (commitlint config)
- Defensive programming: null/undefined guards, explicit return types on public APIs
- Keep functions small and single-purpose; prefer composition over inheritance
- Centralize side-effects (API, storage, navigation) in services/hooks
- Write meaningful logs and errors with context; never swallow errors silently

### Prettier Style (authoritative)
- `tabWidth: 2`, `useTabs: false`
- `semi: true`, `singleQuote: true`, `jsxSingleQuote: true`
- `printWidth: 120`, `trailingComma: 'es5'`, `bracketSpacing: true`
- `arrowParens: 'always'`, `endOfLine: 'lf'`
- Plugin: `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` (sorts Tailwind classes)

### ESLint
- Frontend: `@repo/eslint-config/next-js` with React, React Hooks, Next core-web-vitals
- Backend: Type-checked TS config; some strict `@typescript-eslint/*` rules relaxed in server for pragmatism
- Prefer fixing warnings; if disabling a rule, scope it locally with rationale

### Naming & Style Conventions
- Variables, functions: `camelCase`
- Classes, React components, types, interfaces, DTO classes: `PascalCase`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Enums: `PascalCase` enum name with `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` members (e.g., `RoleEnum.ADMIN`)
- File names:
  - React components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `AppSidebar.tsx`)
  - Other TS/logic files: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g., `auth.service.ts`, `orders.module.ts`)
  - DTOs: `kebab-case.dto.ts` (e.g., `login.dto.ts`)
  - Tests: `*.spec.ts` or `*.spec.tsx`
- Directory names: `kebab-case`
- Barrel exports allowed for UI libs; avoid deep barrel chains in app code

### Import Conventions
- Group: node/std, third-party, workspace packages, absolute (`@/...`), relative
- No circular deps; prefer passing dependencies explicitly
- Use absolute `@/...` paths in `apps/web`; use relative inside Nest feature modules

## 🎯 Frontend Standards (Next.js 15 + React)

### Component Architecture
- Functional components only; hooks for state/effects
- Keep components presentational; push data-fetching to hooks/queries; push mutations to services
- Co-locate small components; extract reusable parts to `apps/web/components`
- Use `@repo/ui` primitives for consistent UI; extend with composition, not overrides

### Data Fetching & Caching
- Use TanStack Query provider (`ReactQueryClientProvider` in `app/layout.tsx`)
- Queries: colocate in `apps/web/queries/*`, use descriptive `queryKey`s
- Configure `refetchOnMount: 'always'` where freshness matters
- Mutations: return server shape; invalidate or update relevant caches

### Service Layer (authoritative pattern)
- Never call HTTP in components. Use services under `apps/web/services/*`.
- Each service exposes `static async` methods and delegates to `ApiClient`.

```typescript
// apps/web/services/auth.service.ts (pattern)
export class AuthService {
  static async login(credentials: LoginInput) {
    return ApiClient.post<LoginResponse>('/api/auth/login', credentials);
  }
  static async me() {
    return ApiClient.get<AuthContextType>('/api/auth/me');
  }
}
```

### HTTP Client (`ApiClient`)
- Base URL from `envConfig.apiUrl`
- Attaches `Authorization: Bearer <token>` via NextAuth session (server: `getServerSession`; client: `getSession`)
- Automatically deep-trims `data` and `params`
- Throws `Error(message)` with server-provided `message` if Axios error
- Prefer `get/post/put/patch/delete` helpers

```typescript
// Minimal usage
const user = await ApiClient.get<User>('/api/auth/me');
```

### Auth (NextAuth)
- JWT session strategy; credentials provider only
- Store JWT token on session; use it for API calls
- Protect routes via `AuthWrapper` and `AuthContext`; redirect unauthenticated users to `/login`

### Forms & Validation
- Prefer `react-hook-form` + Zod; schemas in `@repo/shared-types/schemas` when shareable
- Show inline validation messages; avoid alert()s; use `sonner` toasts for global errors

### Styling & UX
- Tailwind CSS 4; mobile-first responsive
- Sort classes via Prettier plugin; prefer utility-first with small component APIs
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, ARIA where needed, keyboard navigation support
- Loading skeletons/spinners for all async states; empty/error UI states are mandatory

## 🔧 Backend Standards (NestJS + Prisma)

### Architecture
- Strict module boundaries: `Module → Controller → Service`
- Controllers thin; services hold business logic
- All DB access through `PrismaService`
- Expose only necessary providers via `exports`

### Global App Configuration (authoritative)
- CORS from env (`CORS_URLS`)
- Global prefix: `api`
- Global `ValidationPipe` with `{ whitelist: true, transform: true }` and custom `exceptionFactory`
- Global `GlobalExceptionFilter` normalizes Prisma and HTTP errors
- Swagger initialized at `/docs` with Bearer auth

### DTOs & Validation
- DTOs in `feature/dto/*.dto.ts`
- Use `class-validator` with strong messages; transform inputs (lowercase/trim) via `class-transformer`
- DTOs must be referenced in controller method params
- Document DTO fields with `@ApiProperty`

```typescript
export class LoginDto {
  @ApiProperty({ description: 'User email', example: 'user@example.com', format: 'email' })
  @Transform(({ value }) => (typeof value === 'string' ? value.toLowerCase().trim() : value))
  @IsString()
  @IsNotEmpty()
  email: string;

  @ApiProperty({ description: 'User password', example: 'password123', minLength: 6 })
  @IsString()
  @IsNotEmpty()
  password: string;
}
```

### Authentication & Authorization
- JWT strategy via Passport (`Authorization: Bearer <token>`)
- Default-protected; use `@Public()` for public routes
- Use `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, PermissionsGuard)` for RBAC; set requirements with `@RequirePermissions({ role, view, permissions })`
- Access current user via `@CurrentUser()`

### Services & Transactions
- Business logic in services only; avoid DB access in controllers
- Use Prisma transactions for multi-step writes
- Throw `HttpException` subclasses with clear messages

### Error Handling & Logging
- Always throw meaningful Nest exceptions: `BadRequestException`, `UnauthorizedException`, `ForbiddenException`, `NotFoundException`
- Use `Logger` in complex services; include identifiers and input snippets
- Prefer structured logs (consider `nestjs-pino`) for production

## 🗄️ Database Standards (Prisma)
- Keep schema normalized; use relations with proper `onDelete`/`onUpdate`
- Add indexes for frequent query filters
- Use `$transaction` for multi-entity writes
- Avoid N+1 queries; prefer `include` or batch calls
- Use enums from `@repo/db` where applicable; mirror values in `@repo/shared-types/enums` when needed on FE

## 🔒 Security Standards
- Validate all inputs (DTOs/backend, Zod/frontend)
- `ValidationPipe` with `whitelist: true` to strip unknown fields
- Secrets only from environment; never commit
- JWT: strong secret, expiry from env; never log tokens
- CORS restricted by env; avoid `*` in production
- File uploads: validate MIME/size; strip metadata; use S3 creds from env
- Rate limit sensitive endpoints (recommended to add if traffic warrants)

## 📁 Project Structure (Compliance)

### Backend (`apps/server/src`)
```
src/
├── auth/                 # decorators/guards/strategies/dto
├── common/               # config, filters, utilities
├── prisma/               # Prisma module/service
├── [feature]/            # feature modules (controller/service/module + dto)
```

### Frontend (`apps/web`)
```
app/                      # App Router routes
components/               # Reusable components (PascalCase)
lib/                      # Core libs (api-client, auth, providers)
services/                 # HTTP service classes
queries/                  # TanStack Query hooks
utils/                    # Utilities (e.g., deepTrim)
config/                   # env config, routes
contexts/                 # React contexts (AuthContext)
```

## 🧪 Testing
- Backend: Jest unit tests for services; integration tests with Nest test app and Prisma test DB
- Frontend: React Testing Library for components; mock network with service stubs
- Keep tests deterministic; avoid real network/filesystem

## 📊 Performance
- Frontend: memoize expensive components; stabilize props; prefer query caching over local duplication
- Use pagination and server-side filtering for large lists
- Backend: add DB indexes; avoid heavy work in request path; schedule cron jobs for background work

## 📝 Documentation & DX
- Swagger docs with summaries and examples for controllers
- Comment non-obvious logic only; keep comments concise and high-signal
- Keep README and environment docs up to date

## 🌐 Environment & Configuration
- Backend `config.ts` is the single source of truth; use non-null envs for required values
- Frontend runtime env via `next-runtime-env`; all public vars prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
- Key envs (non-exhaustive):
  - Backend: `HOST`, `PORT`, `JWT_SECRET`, `JWT_EXPIRES_IN`, `FRONTEND_URL`, `API_URL`, `CORS_URLS`, `DATABASE_URL`, `SMTP_*`, `S3_*`
  - Frontend: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENT_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_GITHUB_TOKEN`

## ✅ Do/Don’t Quick Reference
- Do keep controllers thin; put logic in services
- Do use `ApiClient` from services; don’t fetch in components
- Do type all public APIs and component props
- Do use `enum` and shared types; don’t hardcode magic strings
- Do handle loading/empty/error states explicitly
- Don’t catch and ignore errors; rethrow with context or show user feedback
- Don’t bypass DTO/Zod validation

## 📦 Example Patterns

```typescript
// apps/web/lib/api-client.ts (essentials)
const response = await axios.create({ baseURL, headers }).request<T>(config);
return response.data;
```

```typescript
// apps/server/src/main.ts (essentials)
app.useGlobalPipes(new ValidationPipe({ whitelist: true, transform: true }));
app.useGlobalFilters(new GlobalExceptionFilter());
SwaggerModule.setup('docs', app, document);
```

Remember: Follow existing patterns first. When in doubt, prefer consistency, clarity, and explicitness. Ensure new code compiles, lints cleanly, and has useful logs and errors. 
